From: Pedro Falcato <pfalcato@suse.de>
Date: Thu, 25 Jun 2026 17:48:00 +0000
Subject: kabi: hide page_pool dma_mapped
Patch-mainline: Never, kabi workaround
References: bsc#1261562

The patch "page_pool: Track DMA-mapped pages and unmap them when destroying the
 pool" adds a new member to page_pool. This is safe, because all instances are
allocated internally. However, it's required to move it around the struct to
preserve struct offsets.

Signed-off-by: Pedro Falcato <pfalcato@suse.de>
Reviewed-by: Jan Kara <jack@suse.cz>
---
 include/net/page_pool/types.h |    5 +++--
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/include/net/page_pool/types.h
+++ b/include/net/page_pool/types.h
@@ -201,8 +201,6 @@ struct page_pool {
 	 */
 	struct ptr_ring ring;
 
-	struct xarray dma_mapped;
-
 #ifdef CONFIG_PAGE_POOL_STATS
 	/* recycle stats are per-cpu to avoid locking */
 	struct page_pool_recycle_stats __percpu *recycle_stats;
@@ -226,6 +224,9 @@ struct page_pool {
 		u32 napi_id;
 		u32 id;
 	} user;
+#ifndef __GENKSYMS__
+	struct xarray dma_mapped;
+#endif
 };
 
 struct page *page_pool_alloc_pages(struct page_pool *pool, gfp_t gfp);
